                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kh0fj9b/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>she promised which is better, but<lb/> they have been unfortunate in losing<lb/> a\n                Daughter. <persName>Isidore Raphall</persName> wants<lb/> some numbers which he says\n                you<lb/> promised him. <persName>Sedgewick</persName> the most<lb/> Plausible man\n                living, I am sure will<lb/> not pay he has fooled me so often</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>P. Joseph</persName> cannot be found,<lb/> have you any\n                clue to his whereabouts?<lb/> I shall expect my commission<lb/> on <persName>Lewis\n                    Solomons</persName> bill whatever<lb/> the amount is which he paid you<lb/> as I\n                have called on him at least<lb/> 15 times for the money &amp; I think<lb/> I am\n                fairly entitled to it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The parcel came to hand yesterday<lb/> &amp; I had to send it up\n                town for I am<lb/> really sick with a cold which has <lb/>stuck to me above a\n                month.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now with regard to your<lb/> new publications I have to inform\n                you<lb/> that I have solicited a good many<lb/> people who I thought were\n                likely<lb/> to become subscribers, but I could<lb/> not obtain even <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">one</hi>. in one<lb/> instance <persName>Mr Isaacs</persName>\n                was present</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kh0fj9b/canvas/p2"
                }
